SIMPLE: inconsiderate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inconsiderate
<hw>In`con*sid"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inconsideratus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Considerate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not considerate; not attentive to safety or to
propriety; not regarding the rights or feelings of others; hasty;
careless; thoughtless; heedless; <as>as, the young are generally
<ex>inconsiderate</ex>; <ex>inconsiderate</ex> conduct.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a very unhappy token of our corruption, that there should be
any so <qex>inconsiderate</qex> among us as to sacrifice morality to
politics.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inconsiderable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>E.
Terry.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Thoughtless; inattentive; inadvertent; heedless;
negligent; improvident; careless; imprudent; indiscreet; incautious;
injudicious; rash; hasty.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inconsiderately</ent>⟦br⟧
